Package: spmixqr
Type: Package
Title: Spatial Finite Mixtures of Quantile Regressions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(c("Kailas", "Venkitasubramanian"), email = "kailasv@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits spatial finite mixtures of quantile regressions: latent regimes
    whose mixing probabilities vary over space through a spatial process, with
    quantile-regression components whose covariate effects are spatially varying
    surfaces. A penalised expectation-maximisation algorithm reuses the 'mixqr'
    estimation core (Wu and Yao (2016) <doi:10.1016/j.csda.2015.08.013>) for the
    component fits and a vendored, spatially penalised multinomial-logit gate. The
    spatial basis and roughness penalties are built with 'mgcv' thin-plate, low-rank
    Gaussian-process, or Markov-random-field smooths. The single-regime case is a
    maintained penalised spatially-varying-coefficient quantile regression in the
    lineage of Reich, Fuentes and Dunson (2011) <doi:10.1198/jasa.2010.ap09237>.
    Inference is classification-aware: a fast sandwich and a spatial-block bootstrap
    (recommended for reporting).
